1) cat: Create new file and write the content and ctrl+d to save the content into file.
note: id file is present after we do cat file then it will over ride.

> svadlamuri@Varma:~$ cat > file1
ravi
suresh

> svadlamuri@Varma:~$ cat file1
ravi
suresh

>overridden happens :
-------------------
> svadlamuri@Varma:~$ cat >file1
bob
smith

> svadlamuri@Varma:~$ cat file1
bob
smith

>svadlamuri@Varma:~$ cat >file2
welcome

> svadlamuri@Varma:~$ ls file2
file2

> svadlamuri@Varma:~$ cat file2
welcome

> svadlamuri@Varma:~$ cat >>file2
hello

> svadlamuri@Varma:~$ cat file2
welcome
hello

> svadlamuri@Varma:~$ cat -n file2
     1  welcome
     2  hello
	 
> concatination:
svadlamuri@Varma:~$ cat file2 file1>f
svadlamuri@Varma:~$ cat f
welcome
hello
ravi
suresh

> Merge:
svadlamuri@Varma:~$ cat file1 file2>file merge
svadlamuri@Varma:~$ cat file
ravi
suresh
welcome
hello

