3) Touch: Create empty files and change time stamp of created file.
note: if file already exists then we create any file with that existing file name Touch can not over ride  it updates time stamp of file 

svadlamuri@Varma:~$ mkdir desktop
svadlamuri@Varma:~$ ls
bigfile  desktop  f1  file  file1  file2  images  names
svadlamuri@Varma:~$ cd desktop
svadlamuri@Varma:~/desktop$ touch file1.txt
svadlamuri@Varma:~/desktop$ cat >file2.txt
Balu
Ramesh
svadlamuri@Varma:~/desktop$ ls
file1.txt  file2.txt
svadlamuri@Varma:~/desktop$ ls -lrt
total 4
-rw-r--r-- 1 svadlamuri svadlamuri  0 Jul 21 10:17 file1.txt
-rw-r--r-- 1 svadlamuri svadlamuri 12 Jul 21 10:17 file2.txt

change time stamp on file1.txt:

svadlamuri@Varma:~/desktop$ touch file1.txt
svadlamuri@Varma:~/desktop$ ls -lrt
total 4
-rw-r--r-- 1 svadlamuri svadlamuri 12 Jul 21 10:17 file2.txt
-rw-r--r-- 1 svadlamuri svadlamuri  0 Jul 21 10:19 file1.txt

Create more files :

svadlamuri@LAPTOP-1BR3SJJG:~/file1$ touch abc{1..5}.xml
svadlamuri@LAPTOP-1BR3SJJG:~/file1$ ls -lrt
total 0
-rw-r--r-- 1 svadlamuri svadlamuri 0 Oct 21 11:51 f1
-rw-r--r-- 1 svadlamuri svadlamuri 0 Oct 23 15:24 free
